Your package gnu-free-fonts failed to build from source in current rawhide.
https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=17718124
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_26_Mass_Rebuild
Builds with fontforge but needs python2, not 3. paragn is investigating.
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 26 development cycle. Changing version to '26'.

I used 2to3 and changed the build scripts but the scratch build not showing backtrace for fontforge. See one such scratch build https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=18106963
Will check on this more in next 2 days.

Sorry I am getting late in debugging. Got issues with my VM which I moved from rawhide to f26 and then issues getting required packages.
I will report this issue upstream now. Will see if I can find the cause that is failing fontforge. I suspect something with python library built against python3.6 but not sure.
